quran[26]{c,v,t}:
  27,56,"His folk´s answer was merely to say: \"Run Lot´s family out of your town; they are people who try to keep clean"
  27,57,"So We saved him and his family, except for his wife; We destined her to be one of those who stayed behind"
  27,58,We sent a rain down upon them; how evil was such rain for those who had been warned
  27,59,"SAY: \"Praise be to God, and peace on those servants of His whom He has selected. Is God Better, or whatever they associate [with Him]"
  27,60,"Who created Heaven and Earth and has sent down water from the sky for you, so We have caused lovely gardens to grow by means of it? You have no other way to make their trees grow.\" Is there any (other) deity alongside God? Rather they are people who dodge the facts"
  27,61,"Who set the earth up as a residence, laced it with rivers and planted headlands on it, and laid an isthmus between both seas? Is there any (other) deity alongside God? Rather most of them do not know"
  27,62,"Who answers the distressed man when he appeals to Him, and removes evil, and makes you overlords on earth? Is there any deity alongside God? How seldom do you reflect [on this]"
  27,63,"Who guides you through darkness on land and at sea, and Who sends out winds as heralds for His mercy? Is there any deity alongside God? Exalted is God over anything they may associate [with Him]"
  27,64,"Who begins with creation, then performs it all over again? Who provides for you from Heaven and Earth? Is there any deity alongside God? SAY: \"Bring on your proof if you have been so truthful"
  27,65,"SAY: \"No one in Heaven or knows the Unseen except God!\" They do not even realize when they will be raised up again"
  27,66,nor does their knowledge grasp the Hereafter. Rather they are in doubt and indeed they are blind concerning it
  27,67,"Those who disbelieve say: \"When we and our forefathers have become dust, shall we be brought forth again"
  27,68,"We and our forefathers were promised this before; these are only legends [made up] by primitive men"
  27,69,"SAY: \"Travel around the earth and see what the outcome for criminals was like"
  27,70,Do not worry about them nor feel any anxiety over whatever they are plotting
  27,71,"They are saying: \"When will this promise be, if you are so truthful"
  27,72,"SAY: \"Perhaps part of what you are try to hurry up will catch you from behind"
  27,73,"Your Lord possesses bounty for mankind, although most of them are not thankful"
  27,74,yet your Lord does know anything your breasts conceal as well as anything they display
  27,75,There is nothing elsewhere in either Heaven or Earth unless it appears in a plain Book
  27,76,This Reading tells the Children of Israel most of what they have been differing over
  27,77,it serves as guidance and a mercy for believers
  27,78,"Your Lord will judge between them through His discretion; He is the Powerful, the Aware"
  27,79,"So rely on God, since you hold manifest Truth"
  27,80,"You cannot make the dead hear, nor even the deaf hear the Appeal once they turn around to escape"
  27,81,"You are no one to guide the blind out of their error; you will only cause someone who believes in Our signs to listen, for they are committed to [live in] peace. convinced by Our signs"